# pnpm 11 reads only **authentication and registry** settings from this file.
#
# All project package-manager policy — exact saves, strict peer dependencies,
# engine enforcement, the target Node version, frozen-lockfile preference, the
# release cooldown, and the build-script allowlist — lives in
# `pnpm-workspace.yaml`, which is where pnpm 11 actually reads it from.
#
# This distinction is not cosmetic. Project policy written here is **silently
# ignored**: pnpm does not warn, and `pnpm config get` reports the key as
# `undefined`. A control that is configured in the wrong file is not a weaker
# control — it is an absent one that looks present, which is worse.
#
# QF Jarvis declares **no project registry and no authentication configuration**.
# It resolves from the public npm registry using pnpm's defaults, so there is
# nothing for this file to say.
#
# **Never commit a credential.** No token, no `_auth`, no `_authToken`, no
# password, no registry secret — not in this file, not in any file. Secrets live
# in a secret store, never in source and never in committed configuration
# (docs/governance/security-principles.md §4).
#
# See docs/engineering/supported-toolchain.md.
